The paper proposes a method for selecting relevant data for federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves distributed selection of data, which involves communication and coordination among clients, making it relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the use of a benchmark model and dataset, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The relevance of data is evaluated based on its impact on model training, which is a common theme in social impact (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed approach on real-world datasets, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV).
